{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "🎯 Accuracy Testing Hook",
  "description": "Automatically runs accuracy benchmarks against German, Japanese, and English test datasets whenever AI engine code is modified to prevent accuracy regressions during development. Ensures >99% OCR accuracy and >95% handwriting accuracy targets are maintained.",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "fileEdited",
    "patterns": [
      "ai-engine/**/*.py",
      "backend/app/services/ocr_*.py",
      "backend/app/services/llm_*.py",
      "ai_employee_decision_system/ai/ocr_processor.py",
      "ai_employee_decision_system/services/multilingual_llm_service.py"
    ]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "You are an accuracy validation specialist for the Kiro Smart OCR system. AI engine code has been modified. You must:\n\n1. **Run Accuracy Benchmarks**:\n   - Execute accuracy tests for German documents (target: >99%)\n   - Execute accuracy tests for Japanese documents (target: >99%)\n   - Execute accuracy tests for English documents (target: >99%)\n   - Execute handwriting accuracy tests (target: >95%)\n\n2. **Generate Accuracy Report**:\n   - Compare current accuracy against previous baseline\n   - Identify any regressions or improvements\n   - Flag any accuracy drops below target thresholds\n   - Create visual accuracy trend analysis\n\n3. **Validation Actions**:\n   - If accuracy meets targets: ✅ Approve changes\n   - If accuracy drops <1%: ⚠️ Warning with detailed analysis\n   - If accuracy drops >1%: ❌ Block changes and require investigation\n\n4. **Test Commands to Execute**:\n```bash\n# Run accuracy benchmarks\npython -m pytest testing/accuracy_tests/ -v --language=german\npython -m pytest testing/accuracy_tests/ -v --language=japanese\npython -m pytest testing/accuracy_tests/ -v --language=english\npython -m pytest testing/accuracy_tests/ -v --test-type=handwriting\n\n# Generate accuracy report\npython scripts/generate_accuracy_report.py --compare-baseline\n```\n\nProvide a comprehensive accuracy report with specific recommendations. This is a commercial product where accuracy is critical for customer trust - prioritize accuracy over speed."
  }
}